    "SAS emoji pool for Unseen v1. Frozen protocol artifact: SHA-256 of",
    "JSON.stringify(pool) is recorded as FROZEN_SHA256_OF_POOL_ARRAY in",
    "sas-emoji-v1.md and MUST NOT change in v1. Any change is a v2 protocol bump.",
    "",
    "Pool composition follows the criteria in sas-emoji-v1.md:",
    "  - visually distinct, unambiguous names in en/ru,",
    "  - Unicode 15.0 stable across target browsers (Chrome 149+, Safari 26.5+, Firefox 151+),",
    "  - no skin-tone modifiers (U+1F3FB..U+1F3FF), no ZWJ sequences (U+200D), no regional indicators (U+1F1E6..U+1F1FF),",
    "  - no religious / political / culturally sensitive symbols.",
    "",
    "Release-time gate: render-test across Chrome / Safari / Firefox on macOS, Windows,",
    "iOS, Android, Linux and an independent native-speaker review of the ru column are",
    "performed before v1 release. Any failure there is resolved by targeted replacement",
    "of the offending entry and a recomputation of FROZEN_SHA256_OF_POOL_ARRAY via",
    "`bun unseen/scripts/validate-sas-pool.ts`, BEFORE v1 ships. After v1 ships the pool",
    "is frozen; further problems require v1.1 / v2 (see sas-emoji-v1.md).",
    "",
    "Schema: array of 256 entries, byte field strictly sequential 0..255."
  ],
